        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 2 at 5:28AM CST by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>A pocket of locally dense fog is expanding into the outlooked
area. Expect sharp visibility reductions down to a quarter mile in
dense fog. Additionally, slick spots may develop on bridges and
overpasses where temperatures are below freezing due to freezing
fog.

Allow for extra travel times this morning and use your low beams
when driving in fog.
</description>
